  <h2>The Pasco County HVAC contractor that actually drives to east Pasco</h2>
  <p>Pasco is a big county — 745 square miles, 600,000+ residents, and most of the large franchise HVAC companies won\u2019t drive east of Wesley Chapel or north of Land O\u2019 Lakes. We will. I Care Air Care has been serving every corner of Pasco County since 2010, from coastal <strong>New Port Richey</strong> and <strong>Hudson</strong> to rural <strong>Dade City</strong> and <strong>San Antonio</strong> — at the same flat rate, with the same trucks and technicians.</p>
  <p>Being based in Wesley Chapel — roughly the geographic center of Pasco — means we\u2019re within an hour of every corner of the county on a normal day. Florida HVAC license <strong>CAC1816515</strong>, bonded and insured, 700+ verified Google reviews from Pasco homeowners.</p>

  <h2>The three Pasco microclimates (and why install specs should differ)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Coastal west Pasco</strong> (Hudson, New Port Richey, Holiday, Trinity): salt-air corrosion on outdoor condenser coils and electrical components. We spec corrosion-resistant coil coatings and stainless fasteners — a standard install here will die 3–5 years early without them.</li>
    <li><strong>Central Pasco</strong> (Wesley Chapel, Land O\u2019 Lakes, Lutz, Odessa): heaviest humidity in the county thanks to the lake chain. Latent-load control and variable-speed blowers make a real difference here — we often spec 2-stage minimum.</li>
    <li><strong>East Pasco</strong> (Zephyrhills, Dade City, San Antonio, Lacoochee): hotter design days, less shade, more rural service needs. We spec slightly oversized condensers for reliable 98°F operation, and often recommend UV lights for homes that run windows-open in winter.</li>
  </ul>

